{"amendments":[{"body":"`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:324-350` still records completion by appending a second `TaskRunEntry`, while the new `update_task_run` helper at `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:419-437` only mutates `task-runs.ndjson` and does not update the snapshot or journal. That leaves no correct completion path: using `record_bead_completion` duplicates every attempt in lineage, but using `update_task_run` alone leaves `active_bead`, progress counters, and journal events stale. Please consolidate completion into one service flow that updates snapshot/journal and mutates the existing task-run row instead of appending another row.","rationale":"The new API is supposed to let the controller update a run outcome after execution. As implemented, consumers must choose between correct milestone state and correct lineage state, so real integration will either double-count attempts or leave milestone status inconsistent."},{"body":"`src/adapters/fs.rs:2340-2350` updates the last row matching only `bead_id` + `project_id`, even though this change adds `run_id` to `TaskRunEntry` for per-run auditability. If one Ralph project produces multiple runs for the same bead, `update_task_run` can silently rewrite the wrong attempt. The lookup should use `run_id` when present, or reject ambiguous matches instead of mutating the last matching row.","rationale":"This is a correctness gap in the new update path: retry history is only trustworthy if outcome updates are tied to the persisted run identifier, not just the broader project id."}],"summary":"Reviewed the diff and key milestone-record files end-to-end, and ran `cargo test milestone_record`. Tests pass, but I found 2 correctness issues: the new completion/update APIs leave milestone bookkeeping and lineage storage inconsistent, and the FS update path ignores `run_id`, so it can target the wrong retry attempt."}